uded as an appendix in acknowledgement of its continuing significance to the representation of Peterloo. This book is primarily aimed at students and lecturers of Romanticism and social history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aPeterloo Massacre, Manchester, England, 1819vPoetry. 0aPeterloo Massacre, Manchester, England, 1819vSongs and music. 4aLiterature Studies 2020. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh  aBroadside ballad.  aPeterloo.  aRadical periodicals.  aRomanticism.  aSong.1 aMorgan, Alison, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2018 eBook-Packagez978311128277040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152613247540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526132475423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526132475/original  a978-3-11-128277-0  Manchester University Press 2018 eBook-Packageb2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles